PARAPHRASE OF THE SECOND EPODE

Beatus ille, qui procul negotiis

[Mr. Sargent made humorous paraphrases of various odes, adapted to special occasions. One only is here inserted, which was written for a dinner of the Harvard Club in N ew York.]
